Calls to eliminate the Electoral College emerged after President Donald Trump’s 2016 victory over Democrat Hillary Clinton.
In California, Clinton topped Trump 8.75 million votes to 4.48 million votes.
Her 4.27 million vote margin in California and her 1.73 million vote margin in New York gave the former secretary of state a 6 million vote margin over Trump in those two states.
They will not work to build support across state and regional lines without an Electoral College to force the subject.